"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Written evidence from RAC Foundation (SRN 010)&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe RAC Foundation \nis a charity which explores the economic, mobility, safety and environmental issues relating to roads and responsible road users. \nIndependent and authoritative research, carried out for the public benefit, is central to the Foundation’s activities.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow does the Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?&#xa0;\nHow reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government deal with uncertainty in its forecast? &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road network? What impact will new technology have?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat mechanisms are there for Government to increase investment in strategic roads and attract new investors? Are there good examples from other countries that could be applied in the UK? How should the Highways Agency be reformed to make it “the world’s leading highway operator”? What roles should Government and the private sector play to ensure better management of the strategic road network?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n              \n7\n&#xa0;\n"